# Cloud agent setup

Start with the startup checklist in [00-cloud-agent-mandatory.mdc](00-cloud-agent-mandatory.mdc). This file adds detail, troubleshooting, and command reference only.

`environment.json` in this repo is minimal (see [`.cursor/environment.json`](../../.cursor/environment.json) — `install` runs `bash ./.cursor/setup-agent.sh` on the agent VM). Cursor may merge other fields; see [Cursor environment docs](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent#the-environmentjson-spec).

## If setup failed

```bash
cd /workspace
bash ./.cursor/setup-agent.sh
source ~/.bashrc
```

## Working from repo root

**Run `bun run build` / `bun run typecheck` / `bun run lint` / `bun run typegen` from the repo root** (`/workspace` on cloud agents) so Turbo sees the monorepo graph. Do not `cd` into `apps/web` (or use `--cwd`) for those root scripts.

For **adding a dependency to one package**, use root **`bun add ... --filter apps/web`** or **`bun add ... --cwd apps/web`** — that is the normal exception.

```bash
cd /workspace
bun run build
bun run typecheck
bun run lint
bun add @some/package@latest --filter apps/web
```

## Common commands (repo root)

```bash
bun run build
bun run typecheck
bun run lint
bun run typegen
```

See root `package.json` for the full script list.

## Self-improvement

If setup or docs are wrong, update `agents/rules/` (canonical rules), `00-cloud-agent-mandatory.mdc`, or `.cursor/setup-agent.sh` and include fixes in the same PR as code when possible.

## Troubleshooting

### "command not found: bun"

```bash
source ~/.bashrc
which bun
```

### Build failures (missing packages)

```bash
cd /workspace
bun install --frozen-lockfile
```

### Wrong directory

```bash
pwd
cd /workspace
```
